cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper deals with deep neural networks in computer vision tasks, specifically in the presence of label noise. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel technique to identify and relabel noisy data, which involves training the network and analyzing its behavior, indicating that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of uncertainty in the proposed method suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of label noise, which could be considered a security concern, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category as well.
